167 - 169 Elizabeth Street is prime ground floor retail which is located opposite the Wintergarden Shopping Centre re-development, the Hilton Hotel refurbishment and the proposed Regent re-development. These developments lie in the heart of the most vibrant retail precinct in the Brisbane CBD.

The property is an iconic Heritage listed building which offers great exposure to the North Eastern corner of the Brisbane CBD prime retail precinct. This precinct is becoming the desired address of high end fashion retailers with neighbouring businesses including Xile, Elio Moda, Hermes and Hugo Boss.

167-169 Elizabeth Street comes equipped with rear access and high 3.2 metre ceilings. The greyscale two tone mix colour of the building provides a prominent presence on Elizabeth Street.

There is the option to split the 557sqm ground floor tenancy or the option to occupy the entire tenancy. These configurations are as follows:

This Boutique CBD offering is a rare opportunity to purchase a vacant property within the heart of the Brisbane CBD. 
 
It offers unique character, from the quaint wooden doorway, brickwork interior and exposed lighting.
 
The frontage is highly exposed and strategically located on the edge of Anzac Square Park, providing a strong volume of foot traffic from Central Train Station and signage opportunities.  
 
The tenancy is 30sqm, including a rare mezzanine level, providing a great opportunity for an owner occupier to create a boutique retail offering including barber, nail salon, whiskey bar & café.
